body.description: Young kids can recreate a classic Jurassic Park scene and play out their own stories with this collectible LEGO Jurassic Park Dilophosaurus Ambush (76958) building set. A cool dinosaur toy gift for grandchildren or boys and girls ages 6 and up, just in time for the Jurassic Park 30th anniversary. It features a Dilophosaurus dino figure and a buildable Jurassic Park Jeep car toy with a driver’s seat for the Dennis Nedry minifigure, plus muddy minifigure and dinosaur footprint decoration. There is also a small jungle build, including an ‘East Dock’ sign for the Jeep to knock over like in the movie and a Barbasol can element to inspire imaginative play. Let the LEGO Builder app guide your youngster on an intuitive building adventure, allowing them to zoom in and rotate models in 3D, save sets and track their progress. LEGO Jurassic World toy sets are perfect for dinosaur fun, featuring molded, buildable dinosaur figures, minifigures and detailed vehicles that let kids relive scenes from the movies and animated series, play out original stories or just build and display the collectible models.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 9, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I've assembled a lot of Lego sets. They're usually fun and stress free. This one was no different. The gimmicks from the movie were funny - there's a barbasol can, a spinning dock sign, and Nedry's face has an alternate "venomized" version. All great fun that captures that scene of the movie perfectly. It's a good looking set and captured the spirit of the scene perfectly. It took about 35 minutes to assemble. At the time of this review, the set costs $20. That's a great price for this set. Legos have become so insanely expensive that I would have expected this to be a $25 or $30 set, easily.If you're a hardcore collector, don't buy this set from Amazon. It came in an envelope and the box was very beat up. This didn't affect the product at all but for those of you that like to display packaging or keep the item boxed, you're better off going to a brick and mortar store and buying off the shelf. Product gets a 5/5, Amazon's shipping and delivery of product gets a 1/5.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A quick hack that makes the jeep look better
reviews.reviewText: For $20 this LEGO set is worth it. Iconic scene from the movie.A quick little hack I did to make this better was use the red lever pieces as windshield wipers. You get one piece for the transmission lever inside the Jeep and another as an extra. I put them on the red fence piece that goes infront of the windshield. Fits the scene as it was pouring down when the jeep got stuck in the mud. It would’ve been nice if the set came with a winch on the jeep though.I think the set could’ve been better but for $20 it’s a good deal.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Legs and arms fixed
reviews.reviewText: My son did not like that the dino's legs and arms were fixed and not movable. The head was also not movable. So you cannot pose the dinosaur in a lot of different positions. My son preferred the dollar store dinos he bought off amazon that are compatible with LEGO, but are not LEGO brand because you can pose them in lots of different ways.
